Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Once the bacon is cooked, transfer to a #small bowl{} and set aside. Keep the bacon fat in the pan.

Return the (now empty) pan back to medium-high heat, with an extra drizzle of oil if it needs it.

Once hot, add the onion. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni.

Once the onions have softened, stir the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1} (see pantry for amount) into the onion and cook until evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and continue cooking until the mushrooms have browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

When the water is boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it from sticking together.

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @plain flour{1%tsp} and @butter{20%g} (see pantry for both amounts) to the pan and cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @water{200%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount), @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @creme fraiche{75%g}. Reduce to medium heat, and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the bacon, cooked pasta and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if needed.

Share your French onion style pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining cheese.

Enjoy!